  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank the influence of geometric tolerances and operating-point variations on the relative hemolysis index; those rankings informed mesh refinement priorities and boundary-condition selections. The screening confirmed that impeller tip clearance and inlet flow rate were the dominant contributors to RH variability, and this understanding is embedded in the factor rationales below.",
